            <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:lang="gez" xml:id="Introduction">
               <label>Introduction, consisting either of only the first or all three chapters</label>

               <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:lang="gez" xml:id="Introduction1">
                  <label>Introduction, chapter 1</label>
                  <desc>The content of this introduction corresponds exactly to <ref type="work" corresp="LIT4017Mashafa#Chapter1"/>, but the gǝʿǝz wording is completely
                     different.</desc>
               </div>

               <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter" xml:lang="gez" xml:id="Introduction2">
                  <label>Introduction, chapter 2: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ካልእ፡ ጾታ፡
                     መጽሐፍ፡</foreign>
                  </label>
                  <desc>The first half of this chapter is identical to <ref type="work" corresp="LIT4017Mashafa#Chapter2"/>. The second half is a translation of the
                     treatise <foreign xml:lang="ar">faṣl fī faḍīlat al-iʿtirāf wa-taṯbītihī</foreign>.  This chapter is also attested 
                     preceding or following the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT4018Mashafa"/> in manuscripts in which it does not form part of the introduction.
                     <listBibl type="secondary">
                        <bibl>
                           <ptr target="bm:Kleiner2000Faws"/>
